Description: A unique fusion of traditional Vietnamese style and modern luxuries. That's the Hoi An Ancient House Resort & Spa. Newly renovated in 2022, Hoi An Ancient House Resort & Spa is a local family-run resort that offers a replica of Hoi An’s Ancient Town architectural style with its clay-tiled roof houses, small streets and water ponds, and provides a relaxing atmosphere in a garden that surrounds an outdoor swimming pool. It takes its name from the original 200-years old family home, that is recognized as a provincial-level relic and is still inhabited nowadays, and that is proud to be the only one remaining in town to keep on producing artisanal Vietnamese rice noodles, to be served in the Resort’s restaurant. Hoi An Ancient House Resort & Spa offer different accommodation categories: Family Suite, Family Connecting,Classic Triple,Grand Deluxe,Pool View ,Garden View and Superior Rooms. Traditional-style rooms with private balconies overlooking the gardens or outdoor swimming pool.

Description: 🔸 The image of Nghe mascot has appeared in many living spaces of Vietnamese people, but is still a refreshing symbol to today's generation. In Vietnamese culture, Nghe had been chosen for the purpose of conveying the soul, hidden memories and aspirations of that time. 🔸 Nghe is a combination of unicorn (or lion) and dog, often used as a guardian and gatekeeper mascot. Nghe can be found in noble places like the royal palace, the most sacred places such as temples and pagodas. 🔸 Nghe is able to show many diverse expressions. Sometimes it’s serious and heroic; sometimes mischievous, squinting eyes as if smiling happily in greeting. Nghe becomes harmony with the Vietnamese people's consciousness, becomes the most beloved spirit animal. And that is also the main inspiration for our brand 𝑵𝒈𝒉𝒆 𝑷𝒓𝒂𝒏𝒂 to be born, with the aim of making Nghe image more well-known for today's generation.
